2.1 filter for padj <0.005

df1 <- df%>%
  left_join(select(ci, ID, group), by="ID")%>%
  relocate(group, .after = ID)

df.t <- as.data.frame(t(df[,-1]))
colnames(df.t) <- df1$ID
df.t$protein <- rownames(df.t)

there are 49 significant molecules in the test table

top.sig <- test.tb%>%
  filter(padj<0.005)%>%
  select(-N1, -N2, -Median1, -Median2)

#   filter(molecule %in% rownames(x))%>%
#   select(-pval)%>%
#   recast(molecule ~ contrast, fun = length)%>%
#   unique()

top.sig.r<- top.sig%>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols = "molecule",
                names_from = "contrast",
                values_from = "pval",            # choose one column arbitrarily
                values_fn = list(pval = length))%>%
  arrange(molecule)%>%
  mutate_at(2:7,~replace_na(.,0))

row_ha = rowAnnotation(III_vs_CNS_inflam = top.sig.r$`('III', 'CNS inflammatory')`,

color scale only for ratio >= 0, the rest is in white

group.annot <- data.frame(ID=colnames(y))%>%
  left_join(select(ci,c(1,4)))

column_ha = HeatmapAnnotation(class = group.annot$group, 
                              col= list(class =c("CNS inflammatory"="#E17A93", "healthy control"="#EAC670", "I"="#1EBC94", "II"="#1F718D", "III"="#103743")))

row_ha = rowAnnotation(III_vs_CNS_inflam = top.sig.covid.r$`('III', 'CNS inflammatory')`,
                       II_vs_healthy_control = top.sig.covid.r$`('II', 'healthy control')`,
                       I_vs_healthy_control = top.sig.covid.r$`('I', 'healthy control')`, 
                       
                       col = list(III_vs_CNS_inflam = c("1" = "#606060", "0" = "#c0c0c0"),
                       II_vs_healthy_control = c("1" = "#606060", "0" = "#c0c0c0"),
                       I_vs_healthy_control = c("1" = "#606060", "0" = "#c0c0c0")),
                       
                       annotation_legend_param = list(
                        III_vs_CNS_inflam = list(
                           title = "III vs CSN inflammatory",
                           at = c(0, 1),
                           labels = c("non-significant", "significant")),
                        II_vs_healthy_control = list(
                           title = "II vs healthy control",
